          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>
                                        <date>10<hi rend="sup">th</hi> March/54</date>.</p>
                              <p>Rev. Dear Sir!</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I have much pleasure in transmitting<lb/> to you
                                        the <sic>inclosed</sic> invitation to the grand to-do
                                        at<lb/> our school on <date>Thursday 23d.</date> Inst; and I
                                        am authorised<lb/> by the Directors to say that they
                                        consider it their pleasing<lb/> duty to bear the
                                                  <sic>expence</sic> attending your visit to our
                                        city<lb/> on this occasion.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">In reply to your esteemed Letter I fully
                                        appreciate<lb/> the kindness of your offer; but if the
                                        Hospital dinner-<lb/>managers did not think it worth their
                                        while to keep their<lb/> promise to the speakers, I do not
                                        think it worth <hi rend="underline">my</hi> while<lb/> to
                                        leave any record of my co-operation (or rather of my<lb/>
                                        pliances) on the occasion. The speech was a good one and
                                        may<lb/> serve again, as “Education” is a standing dish at
                                        our public feeds.<lb/> I trust you will like the
                                                  Toast<add>?</add> entrusted to you.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I am sorry there should be any misprints in
                                                  <persName>Dr. Illowys</persName> Letter,
                                        especially one of<lb/> which I fear our “meek and modest”
                                        brother at <placeName>Cin</placeName>: will not<lb/> fail to
                                        make the most <add>Hebrew</add>. I like <persName>Dr.
                                                  Ill.</persName> Letter; and if you or<lb/> he have
                                        saved the portion I translated I will furnish the<lb/>
                                        remainder in the course of next week; toutefore<add>?</add>
                                        if it suits your<lb/> views to print it please let me know
                                        by return.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">The folks at <placeName>N. 100</placeName> unite
                                        in kind remembrance to you</p>
                              <p rend="indent(6)">Very truly yours</p>
                              <p rend="indent(7)">
                                        <persName role="author">M J Raphall</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>
